        "title": "JPA mapping a composite key with null values",
        "body": "<p>I am using legacy database to read static data where key column does not exist. Hence In JPA entity its a composite column.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>class Person\n{\n\n private PersonId id;\n\n @EmbeddedId\n @AttributeOverrides({\n @AttributeOverride(name = \"firstName\", \n          column = @Column(name = \"first_Name\", precision = 4, scale = 0)),@AttributeOverride(name = \"dob\", \n          column = @Column(name = \"dobr\", precision = 4, scale = 0))\n})\n public PersonId getId() {\n    return this.id;\n  }\n}\n\nclass PersonId {\nString firstName;\nString dob;\n\n// getter &amp; setter\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>So, when I am send JPAQL, I am getting list with null. I know hibernate set null if either of composite key attribute value is null. But as I can not have an option to ensure all composite key can be not null, hence looking for suggestions<\/p>\n",
